# AutoCAD – Laser Cut Building Structure

## Overview
This folder contains AutoCAD drawings developed for the fabrication of our elevator building model. All 2D profiles were designed in AutoCAD and sent directly to a laser cutter for precise fabrication.

## What We Built
The structural components of the building — including floor plates, wall panels, and support frames — were laser cut from **plywood** and **cardboard** using the AutoCAD drawings in this repository.

## Why AutoCAD
AutoCAD allowed us to draft every panel and joint with high dimensional accuracy, ensuring tight tolerances when the laser-cut pieces were assembled. The clean DXF export workflow made the transition from design to fabrication seamless.

## File Formats
| File | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `.DWG` | Native AutoCAD source files |
| `.DXF` | Export format used for laser cutter input |
| `.PDF` | Technical drawing sheets for reference |

## Tools & Process
- **Software:** AutoCAD
- **Fabrication method:** Laser cutting
- **Materials:** Plywood, Cardboard
- **Workflow:** 2D drafting → DXF export → Laser cutter

